 The wisps of smoke trailed from Dean's lips as he opened the door, &amp; climbed down the spiraling staircase. There were pads all on either side, as most of the ravers fell off the rail, too obsessed with the little pink gummi bears running around their shoes.<br>
<br>
With all the skill of a circus acrobat, Dean jumped, twisted, and caught a ceiling bar. This was hooked to seven different lights, &amp; everyone grooved all that much harder as the light swayed across their bodies.<br>
<br>
~Ah, to swing on the branches once again... I love this free falling feeling! Spiderwebs down below to catch me, elven folk to rejoice in my own magickal addition to their show. Now, to find the king again, &amp; find Him...~<br>
<br>
Dean swung from one light fixture to the next, finally jumping down onto a table. Three slopped girls started in uprorious laughter, &amp; held out dollar bills. &quot;Shake it, baby! WOOOOOoo!&quot;<br>
<br>
Dean smiled kindly at them, grabbed a shot glass &amp; downed it, &amp; hopped off the table. &quot;Sorry m'lady, 'tis not appropriate for one such as me to entertain one so fair as thee.&quot; He bowed at the middle, &amp; scampered off, dodging the &quot;dancing elves&quot; &amp; &quot;bards&quot; upon the stage. This was the live music section. There were soundproof walls to keep the techno and the live metal seperated. Dean, with his &quot;extrasensory hearing&quot;, could still make out the general beats of the rave.<br>
<br>
Vaulting between the curtains, &amp; making his way back stage, he found Mike again, or &quot;Michealangelo the Great&quot;, as his &quot;title rightly called for&quot;.<br>
<br>
&quot;Michealangelo! Just the king I needed to see!&quot; Dean exclaimed.<br>
<br>
The semi-fat black man w/ dreads &amp; a very Bob Marley look hugged Dean tightly, clapped him on the back, and said, &quot;Hey boy, good to see you again! What can I get you?&quot; He saw the gleeful look in his eyes, and Mike groaned. &quot;OOOHH no, not this again... You realize you've torn up more than you've helped conserve, right?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;My apologies, Michaelangelo the Great, Kind, and Wise.&quot; He bowed again, in the same graceful way. &quot;I feared for your life. The vile drow had their arms at the ready, and-&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yea yea, I heard ya a thousand times already, maan..&quot; Mike sighed. &quot;He's down at the bar again. He keeps bribin the bouncers for entry. I usually tell them to accept bribes anyways- anyone who can pay high for entry can pay high for drinks.&quot; He stared Dean in the eye. &quot;Don't break my vodka.&quot;<br>
<br>
~I grinned. The elf king loved little as he did his barbarian's vodka... I agree wholeheartedly. As I ran back out to the stage, the bards were playing a piece I absolutely loved! The melody enwrapped my very soul, &amp; I began to move my body involuntarily to the sound. Ah, how elven magicks can instill such pleasures in the mind...~<br>
<br>
The stage was quieted, then grew in an uproar as this dangerous little punk kid ran out on the stage during a cover of Digg. A classic, to say the least, but this local band pulled it off nicely. &quot;I Would love to beattheface of anymotherfuckerthats thinkingthey can change me...&quot;<br>
<br>
Dean roared in with the chorus, &amp; jumped off a speaker into the jumping crowd. Amazingly, he was caught, &amp; not much injury was sustained. He ran like the wind to the long hall filled with pentagrams, red writings, eerie sounds, &amp; a very Halloween-type theme to it. Only this was actually scary.<br>
<br>
~I ran through the Cave of Misery. This place sealed off the bar from the rest of the palace. In case of any intruders, not being of high elven descendance, one would turn and flee at this site. I was the exception, I was told- after all, I am more than just human. Either way, I made my way through the tables &amp; such, towards the bar. There, I saw a dark man with a trenchcoat covering all of his body, save the long white hair that billowed out behind him. Targon.~<br>
<br>
&quot;TaaarrrrRR-GOOOOOOOOONNN!!&quot; he roared. The man turned around, startled, with a drink in his hand.<br>
<br>
Seeing the bare-chested, sweat-covered, knife-happy kid again, he downed the last of his cognac, leaned to the bartender, &amp; whispered, &quot;I'llberightback, baby...&quot; she pretended to giggle, &amp; made a fist &amp; clapped it into her hand as he walked towards Dean. She nodded at him, &amp; threw up her hands in a devil's horn sign.<br>
<br>
~The man approacheth. I stand my ground as I have before, as I will continue to do, as I can do naught but do. I must, for it *is* the honorable thing to do. He may kill me with some trickery of magick, but I will not see it this day. He cannot kill me, not yet.<br>
<br>
I stepped towards him. He queried, &quot;Why dost thou call me by my birth name?~<br>
<br>
&quot;Why the hell you keep callin me Targon er wotever, kid?&quot;<br>
