 ~The bumpin bass chords...<br>
<br>
The trippy guitar riffs...<br>
<br>
The drum rolls, echoes; fascinating...<br>
<br>
&quot;Set your eyes to Ziii-ooonnnn... JudgeYA people riiiight oooonnnnn&quot; Echoes the messenger's voice. Zion...<br>
<br>
I set about at once. The musical notes carried through my body an extacy never before introduced; and it was all because of my own body, my own mind. I knew what I had to do.<br>
<br>
&quot;Tell me Mr. Dead maaaaaan, Do you have the answer-errrrr<br>
How you can get to heavaaaaan, Do you 'ave the answer-rrr?&quot;<br>
<br>
Zion. I would create this place. I would create it, I would be the supreme being, the ultimate entity. I could do nothing else but thus. This was not fate, nor destiny, nor the will of some omnipotent being. This was my choosing, my will, MY desire. I must do this.<br>
<br>
My hand waved. The image before me shimmered, and the notes passed into my body once again. I kept them echoing inside my head, that I might know them intimately &amp; ultimately by the time this ordeal would end. I flowed with the music, the emanations, &amp; my body flowed with it.<br>
<br>
